channel.title: Funniest Posts
channel.description:
Post here the funniest posts you've seen by people on these forums, if you can find them. Here's my favorite one that I think is the funniest:
[quote="Lothy, post:8, topic:291894"]"Your appeal is fucking denied!"
Here's a translation from what they said to what they really mean:
Thank you for wasting some time sending in your offence appeal - you obviously care about your account. It's too bad that we don't, and are therefore sending you this automated message. Waste some more time reading the rules, because we said you should.
At Jagex we don't really examine any offences at all. We just tell you this, because we've assumed that you're 12 and won't be able to differentiate between a completely unpersonalised automatic message template and something that has actually been written by a human. We are so confident with this approach, in fact, that we don't even place your account name in the automated messages that we reply with. We'd rather increase the longevity of our computers by minimising SQL transactions to acquire such unimportant details.
We want you, and every other player, to be positively engaged in our community. Please avoid contractions in all future correspondence, they may be filtered! In short, you may reach a point where we deny you the ability of speaking; push your luck any further and you'll be fucking b&! www.thebanhammer.com for more details.
What do you do now? Well if we were you we'd play WoW, or just about any other MMORPG on the market. There's a good chance that you won't do this though because you've invested hundreds, if not thousands, of hours in this game because our experience system is designed to do that to you. That's right, you've been sucked in for life.
Now go and read our rules again, you know you want to. Maybe one day you'll become a player moderator, where you get to mute people AND remain both anonymous and unaccountable. Speaking of accountability, don't you love the transparency in our appeals system? You have no idea which member of staff auto-denied this appeal, and there's nothing you can do about it.
Have fun - enjoy the community and the game (which is notably fucked in entirety with respect to combat mechanics) - and please don't spoil the experience of your fellow gamers.
Sincerely,
Jagex Customer Support[/quote]
